<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1947-10-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1947-10-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="267" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d267">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10–2847: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1947-10-28">October 28,
                                1947</date>.<lb/>[Received October 28—2:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2149. By official decree Democratic League has been declared an illegal
                            organization. Local authorities have been directed to suppress League
                            activities and to punish illegal activities of League members in
                            accordance with measures similar to those applied to Communists as
                            stated in Government’s general mobilization order promulgated on July 4,
                            1947.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stuart</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>